# Ava runtime state (credentials, thread logs, bare-mirror, secrets).
# Skill directories under data/ that define Ava's non-project capabilities
# (e.g. triage) ARE tracked — they're procedural config, not runtime state.
# We ignore /data/** then re-include specific subtrees; git requires the
# parent dir itself NOT be ignored, so we use /data/** not /data/.
/data/**
!/data/triage-cwd/
!/data/triage-cwd/**

